  · Marginal: passes under at least one regime.
    Tier-1 passes → approaching deployment readiness.
    Tier-2 passes only → identifies the operational safety boundary;
    controller is relatively safer here but not yet deployable.
  · Robust FAIL: unsafe under all regimes including lenient Tier-2.
    These conditions require fundamental controller redesign.
